#

library(shiny)
library(dplyr)
library(ggplot2)
library(plotly)
library(shinydashboard)
library(cluster)
library(DT)
########-----------

df<-read.csv("data_ine_municipalities.csv")
df_cluster<-read.csv("data_ine_municipalities_clusters.csv")

df <- df %>% group_by(region) %>% mutate(mean = mean(avg_month_salary))

df$avg_month_salary_demeaned <- df$avg_month_salary-df$mean

df$t <- df$year - 2003




#######----------

# Define UI for application that draws a histogram
ui <- dashboardPage(

    # Application title
    dashboardHeader(title = "Regional Inequalities PT"),
    dashboardSidebar(
      sidebarMenu(
        menuItem("Home", tabName = "home", icon = icon("home")),
        menuItem("EDA Dashboard", tabName = "eda", icon = icon("dashboard")),
        menuItem("Clustering Dashboard", tabName = "clustering", icon = icon("gear"))
      )),
      
      dashboardBody(
        tabItems(
          tabItem(tabName = "home",
                  h2("Welcome to the Home Page!")),
          tabItem(tabName = "eda",
                  h2("Welcome to the Dashboard Page!"),
                  fluidRow(
                    box(
                      plotlyOutput("plot")
                    ),
                    box(sliderInput("range", "Average Salary Range:",min = 0, max = 3000, value = c(0,3000)),
                        selectInput("regions","Municipalities",
                                    unique(df$region), multiple = TRUE, selectize = FALSE, selected = unique(df$region), size = 20))
                    )
                  ),
          tabItem(tabName = "clustering",
                  h2("Clustering results"),
                  fluidRow(
                    box(selectInput("transform","Data Transformations",
                                    c("De-meaned"), selected = "De-meaned")),
                    box(numericInput("k_clusters","Number of Clusters",min = 2, max = 50, value=6))
                    ),
                  fluidRow(
                    box(
                      plotlyOutput("plot_cluster")
                      ),
                    box(
                      plotlyOutput("plot_cluster_2")
                      
                    ),
                    fluidRow(
                      box(
                        DTOutput('table'), collapsible = T
                        
                      )
                      )
                    )
        )
      )
    )
)

# Define server logic required to draw a histogram
server <- function(input, output) {

    
  data_plot <- reactive(df %>% 
                          filter(avg_month_salary >= input$range[1] & avg_month_salary <= input$range[2]) %>%
                          filter(region %in% input$regions))
    
  cluster_data <- reactive({
    req(input$k_clusters)
    tab <- df_cluster %>% ungroup() %>% select(region, t, resid) %>% reshape(df, timevar = "t", idvar = "region", direction = "wide")
    clust <- kmeans(tab %>% ungroup() %>% select(-region) %>% na.omit(), centers = input$k_clusters)
    
    tab <- tab %>% ungroup() %>% na.omit()
    
    tab$assignment <- clust$cluster
    
    merge(df_cluster %>% select(-assignment), (tab %>% select(region, assignment)), by = "region")
  }
  )  

  table_data <- reactive(
    cluster_data() %>% group_by(region, assignment) %>% summarise(n=n()) %>% select(-n) %>% arrange(assignment)
  )

  output$plot <- renderPlotly({
    ggplotly(ggplot(data_plot(), aes(x = year, y = avg_month_salary, colour = region, group = region)) + 
      geom_line() + 
      theme_minimal() + 
      theme(legend.position = "none"), tooltip = c("colour", "y"))
  })
  
  output$plot_cluster <- renderPlotly({
    ggplotly(
      cluster_data() %>% 
        ggplot(aes(x = t+2003, y = avg_month_salary)) +
        geom_line(aes(x = t+2003, y = avg_month_salary, group = region, color=as.factor(assignment)), alpha=0.25) +
        #geom_smooth(aes(x = t+2003, y = avg_month_salary)) + 
        theme_minimal() + 
        facet_grid( ~assignment)
    )
  })
  
  output$plot_cluster_2 <- renderPlotly({
    ggplotly(
      cluster_data() %>% 
        ggplot(aes(x = t+2003, y = avg_month_salary_demeaned)) +
        geom_line(aes(x = t+2003, y = avg_month_salary_demeaned, group = region, color=as.factor(assignment)), alpha=0.25) +
        #geom_smooth(aes(x = t+2003, y = avg_month_salary)) + 
        theme_minimal() + 
        facet_grid( ~assignment)
    )
  })
  
  output$table <- renderDT(table_data())
  
}

# Run the application 
shinyApp(ui = ui, server = server)
